## Definition

Let $\mathbf{H}$ be an ambient [[(âˆž,1)-topos]]. Let $V, X$ be two [[objects]] of $\mathbf{H}$. Then a _$V$-[[fiber bundle]]_ over $X$ in $\marthbf{H}$ is a morphism $E \to X$ such that there is an [[effective epimorphism]] $U \to X$ and an [[(âˆž,1)-pullback]] square of the form

$$
  \array{
    U \times V &\to& E
    \\
    \downarrow && \downarrow
    \\
    U &\to& X
  }
  \,.
$$

Externally this is a _$V$-fiber $\infty$-bundle_.

## Properties

Every $V$-fiber $\infty$-bundle is the [[associated âˆž-bundle]] to an [[automorphism âˆž-group]]-[[principal âˆž-bundle]].

